<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-08-1471 </DOCNO><TEXT>The adequate evaluation of the environmental impacts of natural gas andcomparison with those of other energy sources requires a comprehensivereview ranging from the extraction of natural gas to end use energy consumption.Introductory remarks are dedicated to general aspects of environmentalimpacts exerted by different energy sources. A detailed survey dealswith the energy sources' effects on soils, water and air. While the effectsof petroleum were found to be moderate and the effects of coal were foundto be of a most serious nature the effects of natural gas on the environmentare considered to be among the quasi-negligible ones.</TEXT></DOC>